{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cbd6862c-8484-413c-9a34-7c845cc339b9","content":"Your project isn't in the current directory, but here's how to configure it. Create or edit `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"--project\", \"src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **`type: \"stdio\"`** — Copilot communicates with your server over stdin/stdout.\n- **`command` / `args`** — uses `dotnet run` to build and launch your project.\n- Your server must use **stdio transport** (not HTTP/SSE). If you're using the `ModelContextProtocol` NuGet package, ensure you call `WithStdioServerTransport()`.\n- After saving, VS Code will prompt you to **Start** the server. You can also manage it via the **MCP: List Servers** command.\n\nIf you want to pass environment variables (e.g., API keys):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"--project\", \"src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"],\n      \"env\": {\n        \"MY_API_KEY\": \"your-value\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ac6deb8b-946f-420c-8e22-ffaeef904079","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project doesn't exist yet, but the user says they built it. They're just asking for configuration guidance. Let me provide the mcp.json configuration.","outputTokens":417,"requestId":"7021:14F71D:14DEDE0:18109E0:69EC1165"},"id":"4e050fd6-30a3-4477-aeea-15da04a6e406","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:57:19.511Z","parentId":"391fbb7f-262b-4e7c-8334-04e14bf536f8"}
